      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "REALIKA (4) looks suited rising in trip third up having just battled last time at Pakenham off a big run first up. Looked in need of more ground last time which she gets now, go close. MORISU OJO (6) has been solid in two runs back, beaten under 62kg in an easier race last time, dropping 8kg off that. She'll be fitter and the stable had a good opinion of her in some of the better 3yo races in the Spring. FOIRE DE TRONE (3) struggled on the heavy 10 at Warrnambool last time but had won well fresh and can bounce back. BURLINGTON GATE (5) has just been fair in two runs this time in but should be ready to show something now.",
